<p>Juventus has on the most Serie A titles, 36, and have also been crowned Italian champions in 9 consecutive seasons from 2011/2012 season to 2019/2020 season</p>
<p>Internazionale (Inter Milan) has featured the most times in the Italian Serie A, 89</p>
<p><a href='https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gianluigi_Buffon' target='_blank' style='color:green; text-decoration: underline'>Gianluigi Buffon</a> has the most appearances in the Serie A, participating in 653 games from 1995 to 2006, 2007 to 2018 and 2019 till present and has played for Parma and Juventus only.</p>
<p><a href='https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Silvio_Piola' target='_blank' style='color:green; text-decoration: underline'>Silvio Piola</a> sccored the most Serie A goals and was active in the years 1929–1943, 1946–1947 and 1948–1954. He played for Pro Vercelli, Lazio, Juventus and Novara making a total of 537 Serie A appearances and scoring 274 times in the process ahead of Roma's legend, <a href='https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Francesco_Totti' target='_blank' style='color:green; text-decoration: underline'>Francesco Totti</a> who made all his 619 appearances and scored all his 250 Serie A goals for AS Roma, a true king.</p>